race.comment: The Kosciuszko form looks key here. CHIDIAC (10) loomed strongly from the awkward draw when giving Clear Thinking a real fright to run third over 1200m here in The Kosciuszko. Gets a more economical run today and winning apprentice hops back on. Due for a change of luck. GALLANT STAR (1) has a good record over this course and trip and goes just as well second-up. Given every chance when a valiant second in The Kosciuszko. Will appreciate Grima's 3kg claim and will prove hard to hold out from the soft gate. MOGO MAGIC (2) showed his true potential when giving them a galloping lesson in fast time over 1250m at Randwick Kensington. Drops sharply in weight and sure to start hard in the market. SO YOU PENCE (8) covered plenty of ground in the run second-up when an eye catching fifth over 1200m in The Kosciuszko. Set to peak with Morgan aboard and gets every chance to run out a strong 1300m.
